[[File:Prof Kljosov.jpg|thumb|2008 photo]]
'''Anatole A. Klyosov''' (born 20 November 1946 in [[Chernyakhovsk]], [[Kaliningrad Oblast]] of [[Russian SFSR]])<ref name=mgu/> is a scientist who worked in the fields of physical chemistry, enzyme catalysis, and industrial biochemistry. In 1989 Klyosov immigrated to the US.  He spent most of his career developing ways to use [[enzymes]] to convert agricultural waste products into useful products — first to convert cotton waste to glucose in the USSR, and later in the US, turning paper mill waste into useful products.  He later helped found a company, and later joined it as CSO, that was founded to use enzymes to alter existing [[anticancer drug]]s via [[glycosylation]]. In 2008 he began publishing work about what he calls "DNA genealogy" that has been dismissed as [[pseudoscience]].

== Career ==
Klyosov earned Ph.D. and D.Sc. degrees in physical chemistry, and an M.S. degree in enzyme kinetics, from [[Moscow State University]].<ref name=PPpressrelease2006/>  In the late 1970s he worked at Harvard University; he was offered a contract to keep working there but the USSR government would not allow him to take it and he remained in the USSR.<ref name=Spiegel/> From 1979 to 1981 he was professor in the department of chemical enzymology at Moscow State University.<ref name=mgu>{{cite web|url=http://letopis.msu.ru/peoples/4652|title=Клёсов Анатолий Алексеевич = Klyosov Anatoly Alekseyevich|author=|website=Летопись Московского университета|series=|publisher=Аналитическая служба МГУ|location=Moscow|page=|pages=|at=|language=ru|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6nWncHQ9L?url=http://letopis.msu.ru/peoples/4652|archive-date=2017-01-15|access-date=|quote=|ref=|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref>

From 1981 to 1990, he was professor and head of the Carbohydrates Research Laboratory at the A.N. Bach Institute of Biochemistry, USSR Academy of Sciences.<ref name=GalectinBIo>{{cite web |title=Galectin Therapeutics Advisory Board |url=http://galectintherapeutics.com/who-we-are/scientific-advisory-board/ |accessdate=16 October 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141121003843/http://galectintherapeutics.com/who-we-are/scientific-advisory-board/ |archive-date=2014-11-21 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>  In the winter of 1982/1983 he became the first person behind the [[Iron Curtain]] who was allowed by the government of the [[USSR]] to use the computer network that later became [[the Internet]], in order for him to represent the USSR in a conference hosted on the network; he used a computer hosted on Institute's network.<ref name=Spiegel>{{cite web|url=http://www.spiegel.de/netzwelt/netzpolitik/internet-pionier-kljosow-genosse-online-a-723933.html|title=Internet-Pionier Kljosow: Genosse Online|date=22 October 2010|work=SPIEGEL ONLINE|accessdate=15 October 2014}}</ref>  He said that he developed methods to use [[enzyme]]s to convert cotton plant waste products into glucose and by 1983 a [[Demonstration Plant|pilot plant]] had been built in the USSR to test these methods.<ref name=NewScientist1983>{{cite journal |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Russians catch the nu-food bug |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XLlzpvKTIjMC&pg=PA543 |journal=New Scientist |date=26 May 1983 |page=543 }}</ref>  He was awarded top Russian prizes in science and technology field: the [[Lenin Komsomol Prize]] in 1978 and the [[USSR State Prize]] in 1984.<ref name=mgu/><ref name=arch/> In 1989 he was made a fellow of the [[World Academy of Art and Science]].<ref>{{cite web |title=World Academy of Art and Science |url=http://www.worldacademy.org/content/anatole-klyosov |access-date=2014-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141021225651/http://www.worldacademy.org/content/anatole-klyosov |archive-date=2014-10-21 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> In 2014 he became Foreign Member of the National Academy of Sciences of Georgia.<ref>{{cite web |title=Georgian National Academy of Sciences, Foreign Members |url=http://science.org.ge/newsite/?page_id=1982}}</ref>

Klyosov immigrated to the US in 1989<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.kp.ru/daily/26535.7/3551840/ |title= Профессор МГУ и Гарварда Анатолий Клесов: Генетика показала - отличий русских от украинцев вы не найдёте |trans-title= Anatoly Klyosov, Professor of Moscow State University and of Harvard: Genetics Show That You Cannot Find Differences Between Russians And Ukrainians |last= Alekhina |first= Yuliya |date= 2016-05-27 |publisher= [[Komsomolskaya Pravda]] |location= |page= |pages= |at= |language= ru |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160528181910/http://www.kp.ru/daily/26535.7/3551840/|archive-date=2016-05-28|dead-url=yes|access-date= |quote= |ref= |postscript= |subscription= |registration=}}</ref> after [[Mikhail Gorbachev]] came to power,<ref name=Spiegel/> and from 1990 to 1998 he was a visiting professor of biochemistry at the Center for Biochemical and Biophysical Sciences at Harvard Medical School.<ref name=GalectinBIo/>

In 1991 he started a consulting business called MIR International.<ref name=mir-summ>{{cite web |url= http://corp.sec.state.ma.us/CorpWeb/CorpSearch/CorpSummary.aspx?FEIN=043138282&SEARCH_TYPE=1 |title= Business Entity Summary for: MIR INTERNATIONAL, INC. |publisher= Massachusetts Secretary of the Commonwealth |access-date= 2016-06-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://corp.sec.state.ma.us/CorpWeb/CorpSearch/CorpSearchRedirector.aspx?Action=PDF&Path=CORP_DRIVE1/2016/0101/000000000/5944/201657331710_1.pdf |title= Annual report: MIR INTERNATIONAL, INC. |publisher= Massachusetts Secretary of the Commonwealth |access-date= 2016-06-22 }}</ref>

From 1996 to 2006 Klyosov worked at a subsidiary of [[Kadant]], where he applied enzymology to processing of waste products from the paper-making industry, and following advice from a friend in the plastics industry, helped create a business that used cellulose granules as filler material for plastic composite products.<ref name=PPpressrelease2006>{{cite web|title=Press Release: Pro-Pharmaceuticals Announces the Appointment of Anatole Klyosov, Ph.D., D.Sc. as Chief Scientist.|url=https://www.thefreelibrary.com/Pro-Pharmaceuticals+Announces+the+Appointment+of+Anatole+Klyosov,+...-a0140816207|publisher=Pro-Pharmaceuticals via the Free Online Library|date=January 13, 2006}}</ref><ref name=PT2004>{{cite news|last1=Schut|first1=Jan H.|title=From Paper-Mill Sludge to Plastic Decking |url=http://www.ptonline.com/articles/from-paper-mill-sludge-to-plastic-decking|work=Plastics Technology|date=October 2004}}</ref>

In 2001 he helped found Pro-Pharmaceuticals, a company that was formed to use enzymes to [[Glycosylation|add carbodydrates]] to existing cancer drugs to make them work better, and was caught up in scandal in 2004 when the company's investors accused its CEO of misrepresenting his role in the company.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Krasner|first1=Jeffrey|title=David Platt wants to cure cancer. Can his company avoid life support?|url=http://archive.boston.com/business/articles/2004/03/14/david_platt_wants_to_cure_cancer_can_his_company_avoid_life_support/|work=Boston Globe|date=March 14, 2004}}</ref>  He joined the company as Chief Scientific Officer in 2006.<ref name=PPpressrelease2006/>  Pro-Pharmaceuticals named a new CEO in March 2011,<ref>{{cite web|title=Press Release: Pro-Pharmaceuticals Names Peter G. Traber, M.D., Former Glaxosmithkline Chief Medical Officer & President Emeritus Of Baylor College Of Medicine, President & Chief Executive Officer (Nasdaq:Galt)|url=http://investor.galectintherapeutics.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=811609|publisher=Galectin Therapeutics|date=March 9, 2011}}</ref> and gave Klyosov a one-year contract to continue as CSO the same month.<ref>{{cite web|title=Form 8-K, Exhibit Exhibit 10.1: Amended Employment Agreement dated 03/31/2011 between the Co.and Anatole Klyosov|url=https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1133416/000119312511090230/dex101.htm|publisher=SEC Edgar|date=April 6, 2011}} See [https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1133416/000119312511090230/0001193125-11-090230-index.htm 8-K index page]</ref>  The company was renamed as Galectin Therapeutics in May 2011.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lang|first1=Michelle|title=Pro-Pharmaceuticals renames to Galectin Therapeutics|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/blog/mass-high-tech/2011/05/pro-pharmaceuticals-renames-to-galectin.html|work=Boston Business Journal|date=May 26, 2011}}</ref> He then became a member of the company's scientific advisory board.<ref name=GalectinBIo/>

From 2008<ref>{{cite web | last = Lebedev | first = V. P. | author-link = :ru:Лебедев, Валерий Петрович |date= 2013-02-03 |title= Праславяне на слонах покоряют мир (Стеб Задорнова и наука Клесова)|trans-title= Protoslavs on Elephants Conquer the World (Zadornov's Banter and Klyosov's Science) |url= http://lebed.com/2013/art6160.htm |language= ru  |publisher= [[:ru:Лебедь (альманах)|Lebed (almanac)]] |access-date= 2017-01-09 |quote= Шел 2008 г, начало карьеры Клесова с его наукой про ДНК-генеалогию = It was 2008, the beginning of Klyosov's career with his science about DNA-genealogy.}}</ref> Klyosov is also known as the author of what he calls "DNA genealogy" and "new science", aimed to synthesize [[biology]], [[anthropology]], [[archaeology]] and [[linguistics]] and to implement methods of [[chemical kinetics]] in [[genetics]].<ref name=l24/><ref name=bal2>{{cite web |last= Balanovsky|first= O. P.|date= |title= Y-хромосома как инструмент реконструкции происхождения тюркоязычных популяций Кавказа и Евразии: научные и антинаучные подходы |trans-title= Y-chromosome as a tool for the reconstruction of the origin of the Turkic-speaking populations of the Caucasus and Eurasia: scientific and unscientific approaches (presentation at the conference "Ethnogenesis, history, language and culture of Karachai-Balkar people", 29 Nov 2014) |url= http://antropogenez.ru/review/812/ |language= ru  |publisher= antropogenez.ru |access-date= 2017-01-08}}</ref> Klyosov described his "DNA genealogy" as a "patriotic science" and between 2010 and 2016 published 10 books in this field.<ref name=ForPol2016/> In some of his writings Klyosov tried to refute the [[Out of Africa hypothesis]] and proposed his alternative Into Africa theory<ref name="ucl">{{cite web |title= Problematical theories |url= https://www.ucl.ac.uk/mace-lab/debunking/theories |publisher= [[University College London|UCL]], Molecular and Cultural Evolution Lab |accessdate= 2016-10-22}}</ref> with "outlandish claims" that the human species originated in Northern Russia.<ref name=l24/><ref name=ForPol2016>{{cite news |last1= Antonova |first1= Maria |title=Putin’s Great Patriotic Pseudoscience |url= https://foreignpolicy.com/2016/11/29/putins-great-patriotic-pseudoscience/ |work= Foreign Policy |date=November 29, 2016}}</ref> According to scientists from various fields, "DNA genealogy" is [[pseudoscience]],<ref name=bal>{{cite book |last= Balanovsky|first= O. P.|date= |chapter= Лженаучные дискуссии |trans-chapter= Pseudoscientific discussions |title= Генофонд Европы|trans-title= Gene pool of Europe |url= http://xn--c1acc6aafa1c.xn--p1ai/?page_id=5166 |language= ru |location= |publisher= KMK Scientific Press |year= 2015 |pages=64–66 |isbn=9785990715707}}</ref> and they have characterized it as "DNA demagoguery”.<ref name=l24>{{cite web | last1 = Balanovskaya | first1 = E. V. | author-link1 = | last2 = Borinskaya| first2 = S. A. | author-link2 = | last3 = Buzhilova| first3 = A. P.| author-link3 = | last4 = Volkov| first4 = V. G.| author-link4 = | last5 = Gerasimova| first5 = M. M.| author-link5 = | last6 = Godina| first6 = E. Z.| author-link6 = | last7 = Dubova| first7 = N. A.| author-link7 = | last8 = Dybo| first8 = A. V.| author-link8 = Anna Vladimirovna Dybo| last9 = Episkoposyan| first9 = L. M.| author-link9 = | last10 = Kasyan| first10 = A. S.| author-link10 = | last11 = Kashibadze| first11 = V. F.| author-link11 = | last12 = Klejn| first12 = L. S.| author-link12 = Leo Klejn | last13 = Kozintsev| first13 = A. G.| author-link13 = | last14 = Kurbatova| first14 = O. L.| author-link14 = | last15 = Markina| first15 = N. V.| author-link15 = | last16 = Pezhemsky| first16 = D. V.| author-link16 = | last17 = Perevozchikov| first17 = I. V.| author-link17 = | last18 = Sokolov| first18 = A. V.| author-link18 = | last19 = Tyotushkin| first19 = E. Ya.| author-link19 = | last20 = Khartanovich| first20 = V. I.| author-link20 = | last21 = Chistov| first21 = Yu. K.| author-link21 = | last22 = Schnirelmann | first22 = V. A.| author-link22 =Victor Schnirelmann | last23 = Yusupov| first23 = Yu. M.| author-link23 = | last24 = Yablonsky| first24 = L. T.| author-link24 = | display-authors = 1 |date= 2015-01-13|title= ДНК-демагогия Анатолия Клёсова|trans-title= Anatoly Klyosov's DNA demagoguery |url= http://trv-science.ru/2015/01/13/dnk-demagogiya-kljosova/ |language= ru  |publisher= TrV-Science|access-date= }}</ref><ref name="kle1">{{cite book |last= Klein |first= L. S. |authorlink= Leo Klejn |chapter= Опасная ДНК-демагогия Клёсова  |trans-chapter= Klyosov's dangerous DNA demagoguery |chapter-url= http://klnran.ru/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/BVZN_15.pdf#page=28 |editor-last1= Aleksandrov |editor-first1= E. B. |editor-last2= Efremov |editor-first2= Yu. N.|title= В защиту науки |trans-title= In defense of science |url= |language= ru |location= Moscow |publisher= Nauka |year= 2015 |volume=Bulletin No.15 of Commission on pseudoscience and research fraud of [[Russian Academy of Sciences]] |pages= 29–49 |isbn= 978-5-02-039148-2|access-date= 2016-04-26}}</ref>

Klyosov is the founder and president of the Academy of DNA Genealogy<ref name=l24/> and self-publishes its proceedings via [[Lulu (company)|Lulu]].<ref name=arch>{{cite book |last= Klein |first= L. S. |authorlink= Leo Klejn |date= |chapter= Происхождение славян, версия биохимическая |trans-chapter= The origin of the Slavs, version biochemical |title= Российский археологический ежегодник N 5|trans-title= Russian Archaeological Yearbook No 5|url= http://www.archeo.ru/izdaniya-1/rossiiskii-arheologicheskii-ezhegodnik/vypuski-ezhegodnika/texts/Klein_2015.pdf |language= ru |location= |publisher=  |year= 2015 |pages= 651–664 |isbn= }}</ref>

In 2013 Klyosov became [[editor-in-chief]] of the journal ''Advances in Anthropology'', published by [[Scientific Research Publishing]].<ref name=l24/><ref name=ucl/>

