{{Italic title}}
'''''Mnemosyne''''' is an [[academic journal]] of [[Classics|Classical Studies]] published by [[Brill Publishers]]. It was established in 1852 as a journal of [[textual criticism]]. It publishes articles in English, French, German, and Latin. The journal is abstracted and indexed in the [[Arts and Humanities Citation Index]], [[Current Contents]], [[Modern Language Association|MLA International Bibliography]], and elsewhere.

The editorial board includes G. J. Boter ([[VU University Amsterdam]]), [[Angelos Chaniotis]] ([[IAS Princeton]]), K. M. Coleman ([[Harvard University]]), T. Reinhardt ([[University of Oxford]]) and  I. J. F. de Jong ([[University of Amsterdam]]).

