'''Roger James Peter Kain''', {{Post-nominals|country=GBR|CBE|FBA|size=100%|sep=,}} (born 12 November 1944) is a British [[geographer]] and academic, who specialises in the [[history of maps]]. Since 2010, he has been the Dean and Chief Executive of the [[School of Advanced Study]] of the [[University of London]]. He was elected a Fellow of the British Academy in 1990.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dean and Chief Executive|url=http://www.sas.ac.uk/about-us/introducing-school/dean-and-chief-executive|website=School of Advanced Study|publisher=University of London|accessdate=6 July 2016|date=2016}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ukwhoswho.com/abstract/10.1093/ww/9780199540884.001.0001/ww-9780199540884-e-22588?rskey=Gixw4q&result=17 "Kain, Prof. Roger James Peter"], ''Who's Who'' (online edition, Oxford University Press, December 2017). Retrieved 19 June 2018.</ref>

